# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Audiobookshelf Environment Configuration
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# 📖 Audiobookshelf Docs: https://www.audiobookshelf.org/docs
# 🔐 Environment Configuration: https://www.audiobookshelf.org/docs/#env-configuration
# 📖 LinuxServer.io Docs: https://docs.linuxserver.io/
# 🔒 Docker Secrets: https://docs.linuxserver.io/faq#file-prefix-variables
#
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Container Settings (LinuxServer.io Baseimage)
#    https://docs.linuxserver.io/general/understanding-puid-and-pgid
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# User/Group Identifiers
# Set PUID/PGID to match your user for proper file permission management
# Find yours with: id -u && id -g
PUID=1000
PGID=1000

# Timezone
# Full list: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_tz_database_time_zones
TZ=Europe/Berlin

# UMASK for file creation
# 022 = rwxr-xr-x (default, files: 644, dirs: 755)
# 027 = rwxr-x--- (restrictive, files: 640, dirs: 750)
UMASK=022

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 2. Filesystem Paths
#    https://www.audiobookshelf.org/docs/#filesystem
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# CONFIG_PATH - Path to config directory (database, settings)
# Default: ./config (container: /config)
# Uncomment to customize:
#CONFIG_PATH=/config

# METADATA_PATH - Path to metadata (cache, streams, covers)
# Default: ./config/metadata (container: /config/metadata)
# Uncomment to customize:
#METADATA_PATH=/config/metadata

# BACKUP_PATH - Path where backups are stored
# Default: ./config/metadata/backups
# Uncomment to customize:
#BACKUP_PATH=/config/metadata/backups

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 3. Network Configuration
#    https://www.audiobookshelf.org/docs/#network
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# HOST - Bind address for the application server
# Default: 0.0.0.0 (all interfaces)
# Production: Use reverse proxy (Traefik, Nginx) with localhost binding
HOST=0.0.0.0

# PORT - Internal application port (inside container)
# Default: 80
# Note: External access is configured via EXTERNAL_PORT (see Docker Compose Settings)
PORT=80

# EXTERNAL_PORT - Host port mapping (docker-compose.yml)
# Default: 13378 (official Audiobookshelf port)
# Access Audiobookshelf at: http://localhost:EXTERNAL_PORT
EXTERNAL_PORT=13378

# EXP_PROXY_SUPPORT - Experimental HTTP/HTTPS proxy support
# Set to '1' to enable proxy environment variables (HTTP_PROXY, HTTPS_PROXY)
# Default: 0 (disabled)
#EXP_PROXY_SUPPORT=0

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 4. External Tools
#    https://www.audiobookshelf.org/docs/#external-tools
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# FFMPEG_PATH - Path to ffmpeg binary (audio/video processing)
# Default: /usr/bin/ffmpeg (pre-installed in container)
FFMPEG_PATH=/usr/bin/ffmpeg

# FFPROBE_PATH - Path to ffprobe binary (media file analysis)
# Default: /usr/bin/ffprobe (pre-installed in container)
FFPROBE_PATH=/usr/bin/ffprobe

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 5. Security & Authentication
#    https://www.audiobookshelf.org/docs/#security
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# JWT_SECRET_KEY - Secret for signing JSON Web Tokens
# ⚠️ CRITICAL: Use FILE__ prefix for secure secret management
# Generate with: openssl rand -base64 48
# Recommended: Use Docker secrets via FILE__ prefix (configured below)
#JWT_SECRET_KEY=your-generated-jwt-secret-here

# FILE__ Prefix Secret Management (Recommended)
# Secrets are loaded from files by LinuxServer.io init scripts
FILE__JWT_SECRET_KEY=/run/secrets/audiobookshelf_jwt_secret
FILE__SESSION_SECRET=/run/secrets/audiobookshelf_session_secret

# Access Token Expiry (seconds)
# Default: 43200 (12 hours)
# How long a user stays logged in
ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRY=43200

# Refresh Token Expiry (seconds)
# Default: 604800 (7 days)
# How long "Remember Me" lasts
REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRY=604800

# ── Rate Limiting ──

# RATE_LIMIT_AUTH_WINDOW - Rate limiting window (milliseconds)
# Default: 600000 (10 minutes)
# Time window for counting auth attempts
RATE_LIMIT_AUTH_WINDOW=600000

# RATE_LIMIT_AUTH_MAX - Max authentication attempts per window
# Default: 40 attempts
# Limits brute force attacks
RATE_LIMIT_AUTH_MAX=40

# ── CORS & Security Headers ──

# ALLOW_CORS - Enable Cross-Origin Resource Sharing
# Default: 0 (disabled)
# Set to 1 only if needed for third-party integrations
# ⚠️ Security: Keep disabled unless required
ALLOW_CORS=0

# ALLOW_IFRAME - Allow embedding in iframes
# Default: 0 (disabled - prevents clickjacking)
# Set to 1 only if embedding Audiobookshelf in iframes
# ⚠️ Security: Keep disabled to prevent clickjacking attacks
ALLOW_IFRAME=0

# ── SSRF Protection ──

# DISABLE_SSRF_REQUEST_FILTER - Disable SSRF protection
# Default: 0 (SSRF filter ENABLED - RECOMMENDED)
# ⚠️ WARNING: Only disable for trusted internal networks
# SSRF = Server Side Request Forgery protection
DISABLE_SSRF_REQUEST_FILTER=0

# SSRF_REQUEST_FILTER_WHITELIST - Whitelist domains for SSRF filter
# Comma-separated list of domains to exclude from SSRF filtering
# Example: trusted-domain1.com,trusted-domain2.com
# Default: empty (no whitelist)
#SSRF_REQUEST_FILTER_WHITELIST=

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 6. Application Settings
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# SOURCE - Installation source identifier
# Used for analytics/telemetry (optional)
# Default: none
SOURCE=docker-mildman1848

# NODE_ENV - Node.js environment mode
# Default: production
# Options: development, production
# Note: Always use 'production' for containers
NODE_ENV=production

# LOG_LEVEL - Application logging verbosity
# Options: error, warn, info, debug
# Default: info
LOG_LEVEL=info

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 7. Docker Compose Settings (Host Configuration)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# These settings are used by docker-compose.yml but not passed to the container

# Container Name
CONTAINER_NAME=audiobookshelf

# Docker Image
DOCKER_REPO=mildman1848/audiobookshelf
VERSION=latest

# Volume Paths (host directories)
# Customize these paths for your host system
CONFIG_PATH=./config
DATA_PATH=./data
LOGS_PATH=./logs

# Host Bind Address (production security)
# 0.0.0.0 = accessible from all interfaces (development)
# 127.0.0.1 = localhost only (production with reverse proxy)
HOST_BIND=0.0.0.0

# Docker Network Name
NETWORK_NAME=audiobookshelf_network

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 8. Secret Management (FILE__ Prefix Pattern)
#    https://docs.linuxserver.io/faq#file-prefix-variables
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# LinuxServer.io init scripts automatically process FILE__ prefixed variables:
#
# Example: FILE__JWT_SECRET=/run/secrets/jwt_secret
#          → Creates environment variable: JWT_SECRET=<content-of-file>
#
# Secret files are mounted from: ./secrets/
# Generated with: make secrets-generate
#
# Required secrets (generated automatically):
#   - audiobookshelf_jwt_secret.txt (512-bit)
#   - audiobookshelf_session_secret.txt (256-bit)
#
# ⚠️ IMPORTANT: Never commit actual secret values to version control!
# ⚠️ The ./secrets/ directory is excluded via .gitignore

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 9. Advanced Configuration (Optional)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Docker Mods (LinuxServer.io Universal Mods)
# Example: DOCKER_MODS=linuxserver/mods:universal-cron
# Docs: https://github.com/linuxserver/docker-mods
#DOCKER_MODS=

# Custom Scripts Directory
# Place scripts in: ./custom-cont-init.d/
# They will run during container initialization

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Quick Start Guide
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# 1. Copy this file:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Set your user/group IDs:
#    id -u && id -g
#    # Update PUID and PGID with your values
#
# 3. Generate secrets:
#    make secrets-generate
#
# 4. Start container:
#    make start
#
# 5. Access Audiobookshelf:
#    http://localhost:13378
#
# 6. First-time setup:
#    - Create admin account
#    - Add audiobook libraries: /data/audiobooks
#    - Add podcast libraries: /data/podcasts
#
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Production Deployment
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# For production, use docker-compose.production.yml:
#
#   docker-compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.production.yml up -d
#
# Production features:
#   - Localhost-only binding (127.0.0.1) - requires reverse proxy
#   - Resource limits (CPU, memory, PIDs)
#   - Enhanced security (no-new-privileges, seccomp, AppArmor)
#   - Automatic restarts
#
# Reverse Proxy Examples: https://www.audiobookshelf.org/docs/#reverse-proxy
#
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
